==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manhandle
<hw>Man*han"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>-handled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>-handling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To move, or manage, by human force without mechanical aid; <as>as,
to <ex>manhandle</ex> a cannon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To handle roughly; <as>as, the captive was
<ex>manhandled</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manhattan Project</ent>⟦br⟧
